The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for vertebrae identification and localization in CT images. The approach involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to extract short-range contextual information and bidirectional recurrent neural networks (RNNs) to encode long-range contextual information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning models for the task suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of CT images suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of RNNs suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
